This demo contains the server side for the Ice Touch 1.1.0 VOIP demo.

A running instance of this server is also publicly available on
demo2.zeroc.com.

======================================================================
Requirements
======================================================================

Ice version
-----------

This VOIP demo server is implemented in Java and requires Ice 3.4.1.


Java and Apache Ant
-------------------

The VOIP demo requires the same versions of Java and Ant as Ice 3.4.1. 
Please refer to the Ice 3.4.1 documentation for more information.

======================================================================
Build
======================================================================

Review and if necessary edit config/build.properties to establish your 
Java build configuration.

Then build the VOIP demo server:

  $ ant


======================================================================
Running the VOIP server
======================================================================

Before running the server, review the server and Glacier2 router
configuration files, config.server and config.glacier2 respectively.

Starting the VOIP server
------------------------

On Linux with a RPM installation:
  $ java -cp classes:/usr/share/java/Ice-3.4.1.jar Server

On Windows x64, with Ice installed in its default location:
  > java -cp "classes;C:\Program Files (x86)\ZeroC\Ice-3.4.1\lib\Ice.jar" Server


Starting the Glacier2 router
----------------------------

$ glacier2router --Ice.Config=config.glacier2
